      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments used bovine blood at 37°C with fixed hematocrit of 35%. Human blood rheology and patient-range hematocrit variability (25–45%) were not tested. Temperature control uncertainty was ±2°C. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric with uncertainty bounds on hemolysis index; systematic bias analysis required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Point-wise comparison of hemolysis index at 5 operating conditions shows mean absolute error of 28%. Systematic overprediction bias of 19% is observed but not corrected. No formal uncertainty-inclusive agreement metric (e.g., u-pooled) applied. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI must be the absolute hemolysis index directly linked to clinical threshold; surrogate QoIs not acceptable at MRL 5 for Class III device.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) in mg/dL, which is clinically relevant. However, validation comparisons also rely on modified index of hemolysis (MIH) as a surrogate in two of five operating points due to data availability. Achieved level 3 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
