      "rationale": "No formal simulation execution protocol exists. User qualification records for the two analysts who ran simulations have not been compiled. Independent re-run verification was not performed. Epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of hemolysis damage model selection (power-law vs. strain-based) with comparison against alternative model forms required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is used without comparison to alternative formulations (e.g., Arora strain-based model). Model form uncertainty is not quantified. This is a critical epistemic gap for a Class III device at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Full characterization of input parameter distributions including blood rheology, inlet velocity profiles, and material constants with traceability to measurements at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Input parameters are assigned nominal values from literature without formal uncertainty characterization or traceability documentation. Blood viscosity is treated as Newtonian with a single fixed value. Monte Carlo sampling was performed but input distributions were assumed rather than measured. Epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Characterization of blood sample variability, donor demographics, storage conditions, and repeatability across test samples required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements used pooled bovine blood from a single supplier batch. Donor variability, storage duration effects, and inter-sample repeatability are not documented. This factor cannot be assessed from available data; epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that simulation input parameters match experimental test conditions within quantified tolerances for all validation cases at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity boundary conditions in the CFD model are derived from pump curve data rather than direct experimental measurement at the test facility. Flow rate agreement is assumed within ±5% but not verified by direct measurement. Equivalency mapping between simulation and experimental inputs is not formally documented. Epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
